modules.description: Provides functions to read and write deeply nested TOML data using partial lenses, which return option types to handle missing fields. Works with TOML data structures such as tables, arrays, and key-value pairs. Enables precise modification of configuration files by focusing on specific sections without parsing the entire document.

Converts TOML data into OCaml values using a custom decoder, handling errors gracefully. Operates on TOML value tables and nested structures. Parses configuration files into typed records or variants based on provided schema definitions.
